    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-06-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Burlingame</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 41.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>, <hi
                                rend="italic">Peking</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-06-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">June</hi> 11, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Perceiving in the English papers by the last
                    mail, that numerous steamers now building in England were said to be for the
                    Emperor of China, I felt it to be my duty at once to inquire of Prince Kung what
                    truth there was in these statements.</p>
                <p>He informed me that eight steamers, most of them very small, had been purchased;
                    that these constituted what is called the Osburn Flotilla, and were all that had
                    been, or would be, contracted for.</p>
                <p>These, he said, all left England some time since, and were now expected in
                    China.</p>
                <p>He could not give me their names, but I will ascertain them, and acquaint you by
                    the next mail.</p>
                <p>I have the honor to be, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>ANSON BURLINGAME.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William</hi> H. <hi rend="smallcaps">Seward</hi>,
                            <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
